article.headline: Idaho State 82, Idaho 61
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Senior guard David Schroeder scored a season-high 27 points, including 21 in the first half, and Idaho State used a white-hot start to overwhelm the University of Idaho 82-61 Wednesday night in a nonconference game. Idaho State (3-5) opened the game with a 16-3 run and led 22-6 at the 15:42 mark of the first half. ISU went 9-11 from the field during that stretch and forced Idaho (1-7) into four quick turnovers. Idaho State led 37-10 midway through the first half and held a 48-26 advantage at halftime. In the second half, Idaho slowly worked its way back. A 13-0 run midway through the period, capped by a 3-pointer from Keoni Watson, cut Idaho State's lead to 61-51. Watson finished with 20 points despite not playing in the first half. Idaho could get no closer, as Idaho State finished the game by outscoring Idaho 21-10 and cruised to victory. ISU shot 72 percent from the field for the game, including going 12-20 from 3-point range. Idaho only hit 37 percent of its shots. Logan Kinghorn added 21 points and seven rebounds for ISU, and Akbar Abdul-Ahad dished out a career-high 12 assists.
